    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>B</td>
      <td>0.9</td>
      <td>0.8</td>
      <td>\(P(B) = 0.5\)</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>If you are not able to tell which case you face at any step, what is the best expectation of success you can achieve and how should you behave to achieve it.</p>

<p>Allways choose action</p>

<p>a1</p>

\[\mathbb{E}_{P}[q|a_1] = P(A)q(a_1|A) + P(B)q(a_1|B) = 0.5\]

<p>a2</p>

\[\mathbb{E}_{P}[q|a_2] = P(A)q(a_2|A) + P(B)q(a_2|B) = 0.5\]

<p>Either choosing \(a_1\) or \(a_1\) leads to the same expected value.</p>
